53.0	Daniel_Pipes	Daniel Pipes	Daniel Pipes (born September 9, 1949) is an American historian, writer, and political commentator. He is the founder and director of the Middle East Forum and its Campus Watch project, and editor of its Middle East Quarterly journal. His writing focuses on the American foreign policy, the Middle East, Islam and Islamism. He is also an Expert at Wikistrat.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f9/Daniel_Pipes_LF.JPG/230px-Daniel_Pipes_LF.JPG
